added.title: BBRAE Part 1
added.description: Beast Boy writes a song to tell Raven how he feels about her.

added.title: How 'Bout Some Effort
added.description: It's Valentine's Day and Cyborg goes to great lengths to make it special for his girlfriend Jinx.

added.title: Love Monsters
added.description: Despite Raven's warnings, Starfire showers love on the adorable twin destroyers of the universe.

added.title: Opposites
added.description: Cyborg has a star-crossed crush on Jinx, the cutest member of The Hive.

added.title: Be Mine
added.description: Beast Boy invites Tara to the Titan's Valentine's Day dance and she accepts in order to destroy all of the Titans and exact revenge on Beast Boy.

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Matchmaker
added.description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

added.title: The Misunderstandings
added.description: Gumball has misunderstood about his date with Penny. He thought they were meeting for dinner but they were actually meeting for lunch at a Diner called Dinner. He runs to the mall but everyone he meets on the way seems to misunderstand him in a different way. Once he finally does get to the mall, it seems all his misunderstandings have caught up with him.

added.title: The Kiss
added.description: Gumball is traumatised when accidentally kissed on the mouth by his Grandma JoJo.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Gumball discovers the difference between a "date" and a "pet's funeral"...the hard way.

added.title: Puppy Love
added.description: Wildernessa's beloved dog goes missing, so Craig joins the search to track him down.

added.title: Breaking the Ice
added.description: While searching a once unreachable part of the Creek, Craig gets stranded with his longtime rival, Wildernessa!

added.title: The Evolution of Craig
added.description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Doorway to Helen
added.description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

added.title: Panamanian Night Monkey
added.description: Apple and Onion must adopt unorthodox measures if they are to see this special animal at the zoo.

added.title: Broccoli
added.description: Some major construction is taking place on the roof of Apple and Onion's building and they can't get back home till it's finished.

added.title: Cousin's Day
added.description: It's Cousin's Day- another holiday the corporations made up to make more money and Apple and Onion are going to capitalise on it.

added.title: Nothing Can Stop Us
added.description: Hot Dog has the audition of his life but he is missing something crucial. Apple and Onion are tasked with bringing it to him and they are adamant that nothing will stand in their way.

added.title: Za
added.description: Pizza's Diner needs a makeover. Apple and Onion better get this right or Pizza is ruined.

added.title: Summer Love
added.description: Panda goes on a mission to return a lost phone to the girl of his dreams.

added.title: Dance Lessons
added.description: Panda volunteers to be Lucy's partner for a dance contest. But Panda doesn't have the heart to tell Lucy that she's a terrible dancer.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Nightmare Hospital
added.description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

added.title: Sadie's Song
added.description: Steven helps Sadie put together an act for Beachapalooza.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: When It Rains
added.description: Steven helps a friend who's afraid of thunderstorms.

added.title: Back to the Barn
added.description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn to build some robots.

added.title: Cherry Cream Soda
added.description: With the arrival of an impossible visitor, Cherry Cream Soda's life is thrown into disarray.

added.title: The Suitor
added.description: Peppermint Butler thinks Princess Bubblegum is spending too much time in her lab and decides she needs a suitor.

added.title: Love Games
added.description: Slime Princess needs a husband or else she'll lose the Slime Kingdom to her obnoxious sis. Finn steps in to save the day but first they will need to win a series of love games to prove to Slime Princess's dad that they are really in love.

added.title: The Red Throne
added.description: When Flame King breaks out of his prison and takes over the Flame Kingdom again, Flame Princess turns to the one person she believes she can trust, Finn!

added.title: Burning Low
added.description: Finn starts spending a lot of time with Flame Princess. Is Princess Bubblegum jealous?

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Rigby Goes to Prom
added.description: Rigby asks Eileen to prom. But in order to get there, he has to sneak his Dad's car out of the garage and get it back in one piece.

added.title: Dumped at the Altar
added.description: The guys have to get Muscle Man married.

added.title: Real Date
added.description: Mordecai and CJ want to go on a romantic date.

added.title: Bad Kiss
added.description: Mordecai finally makes his move and tries to kiss Margaret.

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: Nano of the North
added.description: It's raining in Townville, but this is more than just rain. These drops are actually microscopic robots tearing apart the city, and the girls must find a way to fight them on their own level.

added.title: Members Only
added.description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Superfriends
added.description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Memory Lane of Pain
added.description: While going through the Professor's scrapbook, Bubbles starts to question if she's ever been a hero.

added.title: Monkey Love
added.description: When Blossom makes a bad call, she becomes afraid to try again.

added.title: Bridezilla
added.description: When Mojo and Barbarus announce their wedding, the girls are convinced that they're up to no good.

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Beep
added.description: To help combat bummer feelings, Unikitty's installed Bad Vibe detectors throughout the castle. But soon, annoying beeping detectors fill the halls, and they can't find the source of the bad vibes or shut off the sound! It would seem someone's not owning up to being in a bad mood.Will the friends figure out who is secretly a Negative Nancy, or will they lose their mind to beeping madness?

added.title: Delivery Effect
added.description: Unikitty and gang have ordered some delicious Thai food for dinner.  Unfortunately the wait for the delivery is proving too much, time itself seems to have slowed down. In an effort to get the food their faster the gang utilizes Dr. Fox's time machine, which causes big problems and really hurts Father Time's feelings.

added.title: Lazer Tag
added.description: When the Score creeper traps Unikitty and the gang in his laser tag arena the gang must defeat the house team or be imprisoned forever.

added.title: Trapped in Paradise
added.description: Unikitty and the gang have crashed on a fabulous island. It's really nice and no one wants to leave until Richard convinces them that they need to return to the Kingdom and deal with their responsibilities. Unfortunately every attempt to escape the island is sabotaged. Now they must find the culprit to ensure their return home.

added.title: Prank War
added.description: When Master Frown starts a prank war with UniKingdom, the friends are ready to strike back. But Unikitty doesn't really understand pranks, thinking they're too mean. Can the friends help Unikitty comprehend a proper goof and win the prank war with Frown? Or will they be forced to suffer his tricks without retaliation and admit defeat?

added.title: Belson Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: Clarence is in disbelief when he learns his best friend Belson has a new girlfriend named Pipi. But when he observes their less than romantic behavior, he decides that he needs to teach them the ways of love to help keep their fling afloat!

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naive view of romance backfire?

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: Clarence Gets a Girlfriend
added.description: When Clarence is asked out on a date by Ashley, a girl in his class, he realizes he doesn't know the first thing about having a girlfriend! Clarence enlists Sumo and Jeff to transform himself into the perfect gentleman just in time for his big date.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: Uncle Cupid
added.description: Cupid, too lonely to perform his Valentine's Day duties, comes to Uncle Grandpa for help.

added.title: Bottom Bag
added.description: After receiving a new bag friend, Belly Bag has to realize its nefarious intentions to completely replace Belly Bag and stop it before it's too late.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: Birdman
added.description: When Birdman makes the RV's attic his new home, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to make him leave before they're all driven crazy.
